ion provides a timely look at an established Canadian institution in a rapidly changing world. The editors explore how Canadian Muslim youth, LGBTQ+ individuals, women, racialized minorities, Indigenous communities, and people of non-Christian faiths see their experiences in the CAF. While diversity is a reality, inclusion is still a work in progress for the Canadian Armed Forces, as it is for society at large.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDiversity in the workplacezCanada. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh  aCAF.  aCanadian Armed Forces.  adiversity.  agender.  ainclusion.  amilitary.  amulticulturalism.  arace.  areligion.1 aChouinard, Stéphanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Karen D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeshpande, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdgar, Alistair , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEdgar, Alistair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinn, Melissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorge, Tammy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLackenbauer, P. Whitney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeuprecht, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopour, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMangat, Rupinder, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMangat, Rupinder, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMomani, Bessma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMomani, Bessma, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.g